{"questionId":"9077072","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A rocket of proper length 120 m moves to the right with speed 0.82<em>c</em> relative to the ground.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4de8a16c0efec80b9692479701077e59712b479b.png\"></p>\n<p>A probe is released from the back of the rocket at speed 0.40<em>c</em> relative to the rocket.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the time it takes the probe to reach the front of the rocket according to&nbsp;an observer&nbsp;at rest in the rocket.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta t' = \\frac{{120}}{{0.40c}}\">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>120</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.40</mn>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> ✔</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta t' = 1.0 \\times {10^{ - 6}}\">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.0</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> «s»&nbsp;✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077072","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.4b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the time it takes the probe to reach the front of the rocket according to an observer at rest in the rocket.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.1 – The beginnings of relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}